The paper discusses fingerprint verification and identification algorithms based on minutiae features, which are commonly used in biometric systems. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of publicly available fingerprint databases for evaluation, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the distribution of minutiae templates in a standard format, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
